 resultв†ђobject size arg;size;extent;where;scale;pscale;dthick;Borders;margins;t;tunits;punits;dysize;resize;ppsize;pxsize
вЌќ Request or modify the size of a GUI object

вЌќ Note: 'where' is outside dimensions, relative to parent and using parent's scale
вЌќ       'size' is inside (client area) dimensions, less internal margins, using current scale
вЌќ       'extent' is inside (client area) dimensions, but using parent's scale
вЌќ While object is closed:
вЌќ       Assign whereв†ђ2вЌґ leaves it as 2вЌґ and doesn't change size/extent
вЌќ       Assign whereв†ђ4вЌґ changes size/extent to вЌ¬
вЌќ       Assign sizeв†ђ2вЌґ or extentв†ђ2вЌґ, truncates where to 2вЌґ
вЌќ       Scaleв‰ 0 just doesn't store elements #2-#5
вЌќ       Upon opening, all are resynchronized вЌќ? Do we need to do this?

 argв†ђ##.Single arg вЌќ Make sure a nested argument is disclosed

